quran[31]{c,v,t}:
  38,21,"Has the report of the dispute come unto thee, when they scaled the sanctuary"
  38,22,"When they entered upon David, he was frightened of them. They said, “Fear not! We are two disputants: one of us has transgressed against the other; so judge between us with truth. Be not unjust, and guide us unto the right path"
  38,23,"Behold, this, my brother, has ninety-nine ewes, and I have one ewe. Yet he has said, ‘Place her under my care,’ and has overpowered me in speech.”"
  38,24,"He said, “He has indeed wronged you in asking that your ewe be added to his ewes. Truly many associates transgress against one another, save those who believe and perform righteous deeds. Yet how few are they!” And David understood that We had tried him; so he sought forgiveness from his Lord, fell down kneeling, and repented"
  38,25,"Thus did We forgive him that. Truly nearness unto Us shall be his, and a beautiful return"
  38,26,"O David! Truly We have appointed thee as a vicegerent upon the earth; so judge among the people with truth and follow not caprice, lest it lead thee astray from the way of God. Truly those who stray from the way of God, theirs shall be a severe punishment for having forgotten the Day of Reckoning"
  38,27,And We did not create Heaven and earth and whatsoever is between them in vain; that is the conjecture of those who disbelieve. So woe unto those who disbelieve in the Fire
  38,28,Or shall We make those who believe and perform righteous deeds like those who work corruption upon the earth? Or shall We make the reverent like the profligate
  38,29,"A blessed Book that We have sent down upon thee, that they may contemplate His signs and that those possessed of intellect may reflect"
  38,30,"And We bestowed Solomon upon David; how excellent a servant! Truly he turned oft [unto God]"
  38,31,When at eventide noble steeds swift of foot were displayed before him
  38,32,"he said, “I have loved the love of good things over the remembrance of my Lord, until [the sun] was taken behind the veil"
  38,33,Bring them back unto me!” Then he began to stroke their legs and necks
  38,34,"And We did indeed try Solomon, and We cast a corpse upon his throne. He then repented"
  38,35,"saying, “My Lord, forgive me and bestow a kingdom upon me such as shall not befit anyone after me. Truly Thou art the Bestower.”"
  38,36,"So We made the wind subservient unto him, coursing gently by his command whither he wished"
  38,37,"as well as the satans, every builder and diver"
  38,38,"and others, bound together in fetters"
  38,39,“This is Our Gift; so bestow graciously or withhold without reckoning.”
  38,40,"Truly nearness unto Us shall be his, and a beautiful return"
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he called upon his Lord, “Truly Satan has afflicted me with weariness and punishment.”"
  38,42,“Strike with thy foot; this is cool water wherewith to wash and to drink.”
  38,43,And We bestowed upon him his family and their like along with them as a mercy from Us and a reminder for possessors of intellect
  38,44,"And, “Take with thy hand a bundle of rushes and strike therewith, and break not thine oath.” Truly We found him to be steadfast. What an excellent servant! Truly he turned oft [unto God]"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, possessed of strength and sight"
  38,46,Truly We purified them with that which is pure—remembrance of the Abode
  38,47,"And truly in Our Sight they are among the chosen, the elect"
  38,48,"And remember Ishmael, Elisha, and Dhu’l-Kifl; each is among the excellent"
  38,49,This is a reminder. And for the reverent there will surely be a beautiful return
  38,50,"Gardens of Eden, the gates whereof are open unto them"
  38,51,"reclining therein, they call therein for abundant fruit and drink"